===Origins===
The law offices of '''Goodman, Lieber, Kurtzberg & Holliway''' are a [[Manhattan]]-based legal firm specializing in superhuman law. [[Holden Holliway (Earth-616)|Holden Holliway]], one of the founders,{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 2}} began specializing in superhuman law to aid his would-be villain granddaughter, [[Sasha Martin (Earth-616)|Southpaw]].{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 5}} Seeking her legal expertise, Holliway sought out and hired [[Jennifer Walters (Earth-616)|Jennifer Walters]] (and specifically <u>not</u> the [[She-Hulk]]).{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 1}}

As a law firm specializing in superhuman law, GLK&H represent superhumans in various legal capacities including cases that can run from libel{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 4}} to defending against personal damages.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 10}} Their legal cases also ran into the outer-worldly territory such as across time,{{r|She-Hulk Vol 2 1|2}} space,{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 7}}{{r|She-Hulk Vol 2 3}} and the mortal plane.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 3}}

To establish legal precedents, GLK&H routinely cites [[Marvel Comics]] (especially those published with the approval of the [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comics_Code_AuthorityComic Comics Code Authority]).{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 2}}

===Destruction and Rebuilding===
Looking for revenge against the She-Hulk, [[Mary MacPherran (Earth-616)|Titania]], supercharged with the [[Power Stone|Power Gem]], razed [[Timely Plaza]]. Very few were actually injured, but Mallory Book was crippled.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 11|12}}

Months later when the firm reopened, Holliway had departed in search for his granddaughter, leaving the mysterious [[Arthur Zix (Earth-616)|Artie Zix]] in charge. Additionally, the firm also began offering legal services to supervillains.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 2 1}}

[[File:GLK&B from She-Hulk Vol 2 21 001.jpg|400px|right|thumb|Changing from GLK&H to GLK&B]]

===Goodman, Lieber, Kurtzberg & Book===
After winning a landmark case, arguing [[Samuel Sterns (Earth-616)|the Leader]] was not responsible for his actions due to [[Glossary:Gamma Radiation|Gamma Radiation poisoning]], Mallory Book was made a full partner and replaced Zix as general manager.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 2 19}}

==Cases==
* '''''New York v. Paxton''''': GLK&H represented [[Mr. Paxton (Earth-616)|Paxton]] who was being sued for endangering local citizens by inappropriately storing [[Vibranium|Antarctic Vibranium]]. Although [[Jennifer Walters (Earth-616)|ADA Walters]] initially won the case, the judge later ruled it a mistrial due to Walters saving everyone as [[She-Hulk]] and thereby giving her undue leverage over the jury.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 1}}
* '''''Strange v. Wilkes''''': Wilkes stole the [[Wand of Watoomb]] from [[Stephen Strange (Earth-616)|Doctor Strange]], but later admitted to the theft after being read his Miranda Rights. [[Mallory Book (Earth-616)|Mallory Book]] was able to acquit Wilkes because at the time of his confession, Wilkes was under the influence of the [[Eye of Agamotto]].{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 2}}
* '''''Danger Man v. Roxxon Corporation''''': After falling into a vat of Hard Atomic Water and gaining radioactive powers, [[Daniel Jermain (Earth-616)|Dan Jermain]] became [[Danger Man]]. Unfortunately, these powers were a burden. Citing the "[[Jean Grey (Earth-616)|Jean Grey]] Precedent", Jen Walters successfully argued that Dan Jermain died when the new entity of Danger Man was created. The case was ultimately settled for $85 million.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 2}}
* '''''New York v. Nelson''''': When Bailey Briggs continued to delay the final release of his [[Jump-Jet]] costing [[Hammer Industries (Earth-616)|Hammer Aeronautics]] millions, Maxwell Nelson murdered Briggs. Still tethered to this world because of his unfinished business, Briggs ghost wanted to testify. However, he falsely accused his former girlfriend, Angie Cryer. When is was discovered he was lying, Briggs ghost was imprisoned in [[Cyttorak|Cage of Cyttorak]].{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 3}}
* '''''Spider-Man v. The Daily Bugle''''': [[Peter Parker (Earth-616)|Spider-Man]] launched a law suit against [[J. Jonah Jameson]].{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 4}}
* '''''Constrictor v. Hercules''''': [[Frank Payne (Earth-616)|Constrictor]] sued [[Hercules Panhellenios (Earth-616)|Hercules]] for $168 million for personal damages. Under the advice of Jen Walters, Hercules settled. It was the only case Mallory Book ever lost.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 11}} Hercules later won his fortune back beating the Constrictor at poker.
* '''''Howard the Duck v. Lucas''''': [[Howard the Duck (Earth-791021)|Howard the Duck]] used the firm to try and sue [[Wikipedia:George Lucas|George Lucas]] over movie rights.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 9}}
* '''''New York v. Boomarang & Ox''''': [[Frederick Myers (Earth-616)|Boomerang]] and [[Ronald Bloch (Earth-616)|Ox]] were arrested after the [[Young Avengers (Earth-616)|Young Avengers]] [[Cassandra Lang (Earth-616)|Stature]] and [[Vision (Jonas) (Earth-616)|Vision]] discovered their warehouse was stocked with illegal weapons. However, Mallory Book was able to argue that because Stature had to [[Pym Particles|shrink]] to see the weapons, that they were not in plain-sight. [[Blake Tower (Earth-616)|DA Tower]] had no choice, but to dismiss the case.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 2 1}}
* '''''New York v. Czarkowski''''': Inventor who developed a way to truly travel through time without creating divergent timelines or visiting alternate dimensions. Using the [[Time-Matrix-Alternatizing-Stabilizer|Chrono-Phone]], Czarkowski utilized this technology to send himself stock tips from the future. He eventually received a warning that someone would attempt to kill him, so he preemptively shot the man. However, the would be killer turned out to be himself disguised from the future.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 2 1|2}}
* '''''New York v. Grizzly''''': [[Maxwell Markham (Earth-616)|Grizzly (Max Markham)]] hired them after he was accused of a robbery at [[Madison Square Garden]]. He worked with [[Jennifer Walters (Earth-616)|She-Hulk]] as his defense was to be that he had been seen fighting [[Power Pack (Earth-616)|Power Pack]] in [[New Jersey (State)|New Jersey]] at the same time. Markham, on leaving the offices, was attacked by [[Eros (Earth-616)|Starfox]], who did not understand that She-Hulk's employers had taken the villain on as a client. Grizzly was knocked out by Starfox.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 2 6}}
* '''''New York v. Eros of Titan''''': [[Eros (Earth-616)|Starfox]] was charged for using his psychic euphoria power to sexual coerce multiple women (primarily [[Christina Garvey (Earth-616)|Christina Garvey]]).{{r|She-Hulk Vol 2 6|7}}
* '''''New Warriors v. eScape Enterprises''''': After the tragic events in [[Stamford]], [[Connecticut (State)|Connecticut]], a website owned by eScape Enterprises began revealing the secret identities of past and present members of the [[New Warriors (Earth-616)|New Warriors]]. With help from [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Iron Man]], She-Hulk discovered the website was actually be operated by a disgruntled former New Warrior, [[Carlton LaFroyge (Earth-616)|Hindsight]]. She and the other New Warriors subsequently comforted Hindsight and shut down the website.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 2 8}}
* They also defended superheroes from damages.{{r|She-Hulk Vol 1 10}}

